La escritora surcoreana Han Kang ganó el: South Korean writer Han Kang wins Nobel Prize in Literature
El Premio Nobel de Literatura 2024 fue p: The Nobel Prize in Literature 2024 went to South Korean writer Han Kang. The Swedish Academy awarded her the prize “for her intense poetic prose that confronts historical traumas and exposes the fragility of human life”. It also considers that her work is characterized by a double exposition of suffering, as mental and physical torment, and by its connections with Eastern thought.
La literatura comprometida de Manuel Riv: The committed literature of Manuel Rivas wins the National Literature Award 2024
El popular escritor y periodista coruñés: The popular writer and journalist from A Coruña, Manuel Rivas, creator of a literature marked by social and environmental commitment as well as by the defense of the Galician language and culture, has been awarded this Tuesday with the National Prize of Spanish Letters for the year 2024. This is not the first National Award for the author, who had already won the Narrative Award in 1996 for his work ¿Qué me quieres amor? In this case, what is being recognized is a whole literary career that in the case of Rivas has been strewn with important awards: in addition to those mentioned, and among many others, he has to his credit the Torrente Ballester, several Critics' Awards, the Gold Medal of Fine Arts and even a Goya for the adaptation, six-handed with Rafael Azcona and José Luis Cuerda, of several of his stories for the film La lengua de las mariposas (The Butterfly's Tongue, 1999).
La Feria del Libro de Sevilla reúne a lo: The Seville Book Fair brings together the biggest names in literature for its 2024 edition
La edición de la Feria del Libro de Sevi: The Seville Book Fair, which will be held from October 24 to November 3, 2024 in the Murillo Gardens, will be attended by around one hundred renowned writers of Spanish and Latin American literature. The event, which moves its headquarters to this new location, offers an extensive program that includes dramatized readings, colloquiums, meetings, presentations, round tables, signings and concerts, along with activities for children and families.
